    <item>
      <title>HostContext</title>
      <link>http://localhost:3000/reference/host/t-hostcontext-2/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:3000/reference/host/t-hostcontext-2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Captures the two-context shape of a task workflow execution:&#xA;host services, application capabilities, and the cancellation token for the current run.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;remarks&#34;&gt;Remarks&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This type is the execution carrier above the adapter layer for the unified&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://adz.github.io/FsFlow/reference/FsFlow/fsflow-flow-3.html&#34;&gt;Flow&lt;/a&gt;.&#xA;It separates low-level operational concerns (Host) from high-level domain dependencies&#xA;(AppEnv).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
